The paper deals with security vulnerabilities in SSL/TLS implementations in secure enclaves, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the development of a differential analysis framework, which could be considered as software engineering (cs.SE) research. The use of secure enclaves and the involvement of the operating system kernel in the attacks could also relate to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of cryptographic libraries, which could be considered as programming languages (cs.PL) research.
